"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<h2>The neck may express human pride</h2>\n<h3>``Stiff-necked'' as a term for obstinacy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:9\">EXO 32:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:9\">EXO 34:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:6\">DEU 9:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:27\">DEU 31:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:14\">2KI 17:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:16-Neh9:29\">NEH 9:16–9:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov29:1\">PRO 29:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer19:15\">JER 19:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:51\">ACT 7:51</a></p>\n<h3>An outstretched neck as a sign of pride</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa3:16\">ISA 3:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps75:5\">PSA 75:5</a></p>\n<h3>Placing the foot on the neck as a sign of conquest</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh10:24\">JOS 10:24</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Ornaments were hung around the neck</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:3\">PRO 3:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:20-Prov6:21\">PRO 6:20–6:21</a></p>\n<h2>A millstone placed around the neck as punishment</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:6\">MAT 18:6</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:42\">MRK 9:42</a></p>",
